title.narrative: % OF U5S RECEIVING VACCINATION & VIT A

description.narrative: % of u5s receiving vaccination & Vit A 0- 59 months old vaccinated against measles form 68% to 80% and those receiving Vitamin A supplements from 50% to 80% in low performing regions by 2015., which contributes to Child Health, Immunization, Prevention Of Stunting And Other Forms Of Malnutrition. UNICEF aims to achieve this through Advocacy And Public Engagement, Operational Support To Programme Delivery, Systems Strengthening And Institution Building. This contributes to the following Country Programme result: Children and families benefit from sustained use of safe drinking water and adopt adequate sanitation and good hygiene practices by 2015.
